---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../config";
---

<BaseLayout title={SITE.name}>
  <h1>{SITE.name}</h1>

  <p class="contact-row">
    <a href={SITE.githubUrl}>{SITE.githubLabel}</a>
    <span class="sep">·</span>
    <span>{SITE.emailDisplay}</span>
  </p>

  <p>
    I'm an undergraduate at UC Berkeley broadly interested in optimization, from
    theoretical algorithms to efficient machine learning systems. I previously
    worked on personal projects including a competitive chess engine, and now
    mainly work on research in efficient ML.
  </p>

  <p>
    I come from a competitive programming background, so I enjoy working from
    theory and first principles. More recently, I've been moving closer to
    systems and hardware aligned efficiency. Outside of technical work, I play chess and piano. 
    I also bake, not particularly well, but I can make some decent macarons :D.
  </p>

  <section>
    <h2>Currently</h2>
    <p>
      I'm interning at MatX as an ML researcher, working on sparse attention
      methods that shift LLM decoding away from the memory-bound regime by
      reducing the number of KV cache entries loaded at each step. I'm also an
      undergraduate researcher at BAIR in the Pallas group, where I work on
      making video generation more efficient through VAE optimization and sparse
      methods for diffusion language models. At Berkeley, I'm involved in
      Machine Learning at Berkeley through the education and research committees.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Selected work</h2>
    <dl class="worklist">
      <dt>Altair Chess Engine</dt>
      <dd>
        A formerly top-30, 3600+ rated chess engine in C++, downloaded over 3000
        times and competitive in the CCC and TCEC tournaments.
      </dd>

      <dt>Annapurna Labs</dt>
      <dd>
        Fused NKI kernels for attention and 3D-RoPE on AWS Trainium 2, with
        roofline analysis and MFU optimization for video diffusion inference.
      </dd>
    </dl>
    <p class="more-link">
      <a href="/projects">All projects →</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
